    "content": "<html lang=\"en\">\n<head>\n<meta charset=\"UTF-8\" />\n<meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1\" />\n<title>JavaScript Indexing Demonstration</title>\n<style>\n  body {\n    font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\n    margin: 30px;\n    background: #f9f9f9;\n  }\n  h1 {\n    color: #2c3e50;\n  }\n  .container {\n    background: white;\n    padding: 20px;\n    border-radius: 8px;\n    box-shadow: 0 2px 8px rgba(0,0,0,0.1);\n    max-width: 700px;\n    margin: auto;\n  }\n  input, button {\n    font-size: 16px;\n    padding: 8px;\n    margin-top: 8px;\n  }\n  .result {\n    margin-top: 20px;\n    background: #e8f0fe;\n    padding: 15px;\n    border-radius: 5px;\n    border: 1px solid #a3c1f7;\n  }\n  code {\n    background: #eee;\n    padding: 2px 4px;\n    border-radius: 3px;\n    font-size: 14px;\n  }\n</style>\n</head>\n<body>\n  <div class=\"container\">\n    <h1>JavaScript Indexing Demonstration</h1>\n    <p>\n      Indexing in JavaScript is a way to access individual elements of strings or arrays by their <strong>position</strong>. Positions (indexes) start at <code>0</code>, meaning the first element has index 0, the second index 1, and so on.\n    </p>\n\n    <h2>Example Array</h2>\n    <p>Consider the array:</p>\n    <pre><code>let fruits = [\"Apple\", \"Banana\", \"Cherry\", \"Date\", \"Elderberry\"];</code></pre>\n\n    <h3>Try it yourself:</h3>\n    <label for=\"indexInput\">Enter an index (0 to 4): </label>\n    <input type=\"number\" id=\"indexInput\" min=\"0\" max=\"4\" value=\"0\" />\n    <button onclick=\"showIndexedElement()\">Show element at index</button>\n\n    <div class=\"result\" id=\"result\"></div>\n\n    <h2>String Indexing</h2>\n    <p>\n      Strings behave like arrays of characters. You can access each character by its index.\n    </p>\n\n    <pre><code>let greeting = \"Hello\";\nconsole.log(greeting[0]); // \"H\"\nconsole.log(greeting[4]); // \"o\"\n</code></pre>\n  </div>\n\n<script>\n  const fruits = [\"Apple\", \"Banana\", \"Cherry\", \"Date\", \"Elderberry\"];\n  const resultDiv = document.getElementById('result');\n\n  function showIndexedElement() {\n    const input = document.getElementById('indexInput');\n    const index = Number(input.value);\n\n    if (isNaN(index) || index < 0 || index >= fruits.length) {\n      resultDiv.textContent = \"Please enter a valid index between 0 and \" + (fruits.length - 1) + \".\";\n      resultDiv.style.color = 'red';\n      return;\n    }\n\n    const element = fruits[index];\n    resultDiv.style.color = 'black';\n    resultDiv.innerHTML =\n      `<strong>fruits[${index}]</strong> is: <code>${element}</code>`;\n  }\n</script>\n</body>\n</html>"
